ramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":13,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Multon IV of Gilsland was born on 21 February 1276, in Northumberland, England, his father, Thomas Multon III of Gilsland, was 10 and his mother, Isabel, was 12. He had at least 1 daughter with Margaret Mauley. He died on 26 November 1313, in Gilsland, Northumberland, England, at the age of 37."},"et":{"21 February 1276–26 November 1313":"21. veebruar 1276–26. november 1313","1276–1313":"1276–1313","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1284–Female":"1284–Surnud","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1267–1295":"1267–1295","1265–1328":"1265–1328","20 July 1300":"20. juuli 1300","12 February 1295":"12. veebruar 1295","about 1281":"umbes 1281","21 February 1276":"21. veebruar 1276","1285":"1285","1295":"1295","1361":"1361","1284":"1284","1290":"1290","1313":"1313","26 November 1313":"26. november 1313","1267":"1267","1300":"1300","1265":"1265","1276":"1276","22 May 1306":"22. mai 1306","1328":"1328","Mulgrave Castle, Yorkshire, England":"Mulgrave Castle, Yorkshire, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Naworth, Cumbria, England, United Kingdom":"Naworth, Cumbria, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aquitaine, France":"Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"21 February 1276–26 November 1313":"21. helmikuuta 1276–26. marraskuuta 1313","1276–1313":"1276–1313","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1284–Female":"1284–Kuollut","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1267–1295":"1267–1295","1265–1328":"1265–1328","20 July 1300":"20. heinäkuuta 1300","12 February 1295":"12. helmikuuta 1295","ab